      "text": "Definition and Usage",
      "level": "h2"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "The $root object represents the Vue instance of the root component of the total Vue application.",
      "html": "<p>The <code>$root</code> object represents the Vue instance of the root component of the total Vue application.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "When the $root object is used in the root component, it simply refers to the instance of that component itself.",
      "html": "<p>When the <code>$root</code> object is used in the root component, it simply refers to the instance of that component itself.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "We can use the $root object to access the root instance directly from a child component, even far down the component tree structure, to call methods, read or manipulate data properties, and so on.",
      "html": "<p>We can use the <code>$root</code> object to access the root instance directly from a child component, even far down the component tree structure, to call methods, read or manipulate data properties, and so on.</p>"
    },
